{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GmAhAvfkXVH6JeCjpooAPi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Shared E2E page-object helpers for coinflip tests.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * CSS-class-based selectors matching the actual component markup.\n     5→ * Provides create, join, claim, cancel actions and reusable wait/assert primitives.\n     6→ */\n     7→import { type Page, type Locator, expect } from \"@playwright/test\";\n     8→\n     9→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    10→// Selectors (CSS classes from CoinflipPage, ActiveMatchView, OpenMatchesList)\n    11→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    12→\n    13→export const sel = {\n    14→  // Page structure\n    15→  lobby: \".coinflip-lobby\",\n    16→  sidebar: \".coinflip-sidebar\",\n    17→  main: \".coinflip-main\",\n    18→\n    19→  // Sidebar — create flow\n    20→  sidebarTitle: \".coinflip-sidebar__title\",\n    21→  tierSelector: \".rng-tier-selector\",\n    22→  tierButton: (tier: string) => `.rng-tier-btn:has(.rng-tier-gem--${tier})`,\n    23→  tierButtonSelected: \".rng-tier-btn--selected\",\n    24→  sideSelector: \".coinflip-side-selector\",\n    25→  sideButtonHeads: \".coinflip-side-btn--heads\",\n    26→  sideButtonTails: \".coinflip-side-btn--tails\",\n    27→  sideButtonSelected: \".coinflip-side-btn--selected\",\n    28→  summary: \".coinflip-sidebar__summary\",\n    29→  actionButton: \".coinflip-action-btn\",\n    30→  actionButtonSecondary: \".coinflip-action-btn--secondary\",\n    31→\n    32→  // Lobby — open matches\n    33→  matchesList: \".coinflip-matches__list\",\n    34→  matchesCount: \".coinflip-matches__count\",\n    35→  matchCard: \".coinflip-match-card\",\n    36→  matchCardOwn: \".coinflip-match-card--own\",\n    37→  matchCardClaimable: \".coinflip-match-card--claimable\",\n    38→  matchCardJoinBtn: \".coinflip-match-card__join-btn\",\n    39→  matchCardAmount: \".coinflip-match-card__amount\",\n    40→  matchCardAddress: \".coinflip-match-card__address\",\n    41→\n    42→  // Active match view\n    43→  activeMatch: \".coinflip-active-match\",\n    44→  activeMatchTitle: \".coinflip-active-match__title\",\n    45→  activeMatchTitleWon: \".coinflip-active-match__title--won\",\n    46→  activeMatchTitleLost: \".coinflip-active-match__title--lost\",\n    47→  activeMatchWaiting: \".coinflip-active-match__waiting\",\n    48→  activeMatchPlaying: \".coinflip-active-match__playing\",\n    49→\n    50→  // Result\n    51→  resultOutcome: \".coinflip-result__outcome\",\n    52→  resultPayout: \".coinflip-result__payout\",\n    53→\n    54→  // Post-claim\n    55→  postClaim: \".coinflip-active-match__post-claim\",\n    56→\n    57→  // Error\n    58→  errorToast: \".coinflip-error-toast\",\n    59→  toastMessage: \".rng-toast__message\",\n    60→\n    61→  // Sidebar — active match info\n    62→  sidebarStatus: \".coinflip-sidebar__status\",\n    63→  sidebarPot: \".coinflip-sidebar__pot\",\n    64→} as const;\n    65→\n    66→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    67→// Types\n    68→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    69→\n    70→export type CoinSide = \"heads\" | \"tails\";\n    71→export type Tier =\n    72→  | \"iron\"\n    73→  | \"bronze\"\n    74→  | \"silver\"\n    75→  | \"gold\"\n    76→  | \"platinum\"\n    77→  | \"diamond\";\n    78→\n    79→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    80→// Page-object actions\n    81→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    82→\n    83→/**\n    84→ * Navigate to the coinflip page and wait for the lobby to render.\n    85→ */\n    86→export async function navigateToCoinflip(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n    87→  await page.goto(\"/coinflip\", { waitUntil: \"networkidle\" });\n    88→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.main, { state: \"visible\", timeout: 10_000 });\n    89→}\n    90→\n    91→/**\n    92→ * Select a tier in the sidebar tier selector.\n    93→ */\n    94→export async function selectTier(page: Page, tier: Tier): Promise<void> {\n    95→  await page.click(sel.tierButton(tier));\n    96→  await expect(page.locator(sel.tierButton(tier))).toHaveClass(/rng-tier-btn--selected/);\n    97→}\n    98→\n    99→/**\n   100→ * Select a coin side (heads or tails) in the sidebar.\n   101→ */\n   102→export async function selectSide(page: Page, side: CoinSide): Promise<void> {\n   103→  const selector =\n   104→    side === \"heads\" ? sel.sideButtonHeads : sel.sideButtonTails;\n   105→  await page.click(selector);\n   106→  await expect(page.locator(selector)).toHaveClass(/coinflip-side-btn--selected/);\n   107→}\n   108→\n   109→/**\n   110→ * Create a match: select tier, select side, click \"Create Game\".\n   111→ * Returns when the active match view (waiting state) is visible.\n   112→ */\n   113→export async function createMatch(\n   114→  page: Page,\n   115→  tier: Tier,\n   116→  side: CoinSide,\n   117→): Promise<void> {\n   118→  await selectTier(page, tier);\n   119→  await selectSide(page, side);\n   120→\n   121→  // Click create — button text is \"Create Game\"\n   122→  const createBtn = page.locator(sel.actionButton, {\n   123→    hasText: \"Create Game\",\n   124→  });\n   125→  await expect(createBtn).toBeEnabled();\n   126→  await createBtn.click();\n   127→\n   128→  // Wait for transition to active match (waiting for opponent)\n   129→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.activeMatch, {\n   130→    state: \"visible\",\n   131→    timeout: 15_000,\n   132→  });\n   133→}\n   134→\n   135→/**\n   136→ * Join a match visible in the lobby. If `matchIndex` is provided, join that\n   137→ * specific card (0-based). Otherwise joins the first joinable match.\n   138→ */\n   139→export async function joinMatch(\n   140→  page: Page,\n   141→  matchIndex = 0,\n   142→): Promise<void> {\n   143→  const cards = page.locator(\n   144→    `${sel.matchCard}:not(${sel.matchCardOwn}):not(${sel.matchCardClaimable})`,\n   145→  );\n   146→  const joinBtn = cards.nth(matchIndex).locator(sel.matchCardJoinBtn);\n   147→  await expect(joinBtn).toBeEnabled({ timeout: 10_000 });\n   148→  await joinBtn.click();\n   149→\n   150→  // Wait for active match view to appear\n   151→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.activeMatch, {\n   152→    state: \"visible\",\n   153→    timeout: 15_000,\n   154→  });\n   155→}\n   156→\n   157→/**\n   158→ * Cancel the currently active match (phase = \"created\", waiting for opponent).\n   159→ * Clicks \"Cancel Match\" button in the ActiveMatchView.\n   160→ */\n   161→export async function cancelMatch(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   162→  const cancelBtn = page.locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Cancel Match\" });\n   163→  await expect(cancelBtn).toBeVisible({ timeout: 5_000 });\n   164→  await cancelBtn.click();\n   165→\n   166→  // Wait for lobby to reappear\n   167→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, {\n   168→    state: \"visible\",\n   169→    timeout: 15_000,\n   170→  });\n   171→}\n   172→\n   173→/**\n   174→ * Claim payout for the winner, or settle for the loser.\n   175→ * Clicks the \"Claim Payout\" or \"Settle & Return\" button in the sidebar.\n   176→ */\n   177→export async function claimOrSettle(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   178→  // The claim/settle button is in the sidebar (CoinflipPage renders it there)\n   179→  const claimBtn = page.locator(sel.sidebar).locator(sel.actionButton).first();\n   180→  await expect(claimBtn).toBeEnabled({ timeout: 15_000 });\n   181→  await claimBtn.click();\n   182→\n   183→  // Wait for \"Back to Lobby\" button to confirm claim completed\n   184→  await expect(\n   185→    page.locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Back to Lobby\" }),\n   186→  ).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });\n   187→}\n   188→\n   189→/**\n   190→ * Click \"Back to Lobby\" to return after claiming.\n   191→ */\n   192→export async function backToLobby(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   193→  const btn = page.locator(\"button\", { hasText: \"Back to Lobby\" });\n   194→  await expect(btn).toBeVisible();\n   195→  await btn.click();\n   196→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, {\n   197→    state: \"visible\",\n   198→    timeout: 10_000,\n   199→  });\n   200→}\n   201→\n   202→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   203→// Wait / assert primitives\n   204→// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n   205→\n   206→/**\n   207→ * Wait until the sidebar status text matches the expected phase label.\n   208→ * Phase labels: \"Waiting...\", \"Ready!\", \"Countdown...\", \"Flipping...\", \"Complete\"\n   209→ */\n   210→export async function waitForPhaseLabel(\n   211→  page: Page,\n   212→  label: string,\n   213→  timeout = 30_000,\n   214→): Promise<void> {\n   215→  await expect(page.locator(sel.sidebarStatus)).toHaveText(label, {\n   216→    timeout,\n   217→  });\n   218→}\n   219→\n   220→/**\n   221→ * Wait for the active match title to indicate a win or loss.\n   222→ */\n   223→export async function waitForResult(\n   224→  page: Page,\n   225→  timeout = 30_000,\n   226→): Promise<\"won\" | \"lost\"> {\n   227→  // Wait for either won or lost title class to appear\n   228→  const wonLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleWon);\n   229→  const lostLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleLost);\n   230→\n   231→  await expect(wonLocator.or(lostLocator)).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   232→\n   233→  if (await wonLocator.isVisible()) return \"won\";\n   234→  return \"lost\";\n   235→}\n   236→\n   237→/**\n   238→ * Wait for a match to appear in the lobby's open match list.\n   239→ */\n   240→export async function waitForLobbyMatch(\n   241→  page: Page,\n   242→  timeout = 15_000,\n   243→): Promise<Locator> {\n   244→  const card = page.locator(\n   245→    `${sel.matchCard}:not(${sel.matchCardClaimable})`,\n   246→  ).first();\n   247→  await expect(card).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   248→  return card;\n   249→}\n   250→\n   251→/**\n   252→ * Assert the lobby is empty (no open matches).\n   253→ */\n   254→export async function assertLobbyEmpty(\n   255→  page: Page,\n   256→  timeout = 10_000,\n   257→): Promise<void> {\n   258→  // Either the empty state text or zero non-claimable match cards\n   259→  await expect(\n   260→    page.locator(`${sel.matchCard}:not(${sel.matchCardClaimable})`),\n   261→  ).toHaveCount(0, { timeout });\n   262→}\n   263→\n   264→/**\n   265→ * Assert that an error toast is visible with the given message substring.\n   266→ */\n   267→export async function assertErrorToast(\n   268→  page: Page,\n   269→  messageSubstring: string,\n   270→  timeout = 5_000,\n   271→): Promise<void> {\n   272→  const toast = page.locator(sel.errorToast);\n   273→  await expect(toast).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   274→  await expect(toast).toContainText(messageSubstring);\n   275→}\n   276→\n   277→/**\n   278→ * Assert that no error toasts are visible.\n   279→ */\n   280→export async function assertNoErrorToast(page: Page): Promise<void> {\n   281→  await expect(page.locator(sel.errorToast)).toHaveCount(0);\n   282→}\n   283→\n   284→/**\n   285→ * Get the current balance displayed or fetched from connection for a wallet.\n   286→ * This is a convenience wrapper for reading SOL balance via RPC, not UI-based.\n   287→ */\n   288→export async function getSolBalance(\n   289→  page: Page,\n   290→  walletAddress: string,\n   291→  rpcUrl = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\",\n   292→): Promise<number> {\n   293→  return page.evaluate(\n   294→    async ({ address, rpc }) => {\n   295→      const res = await fetch(rpc, {\n   296→        method: \"POST\",\n   297→        headers: { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" },\n   298→        body: JSON.stringify({\n   299→          jsonrpc: \"2.0\",\n   300→          id: 1,\n   301→          method: \"getBalance\",\n   302→          params: [address, { commitment: \"confirmed\" }],\n   303→        }),\n   304→      });\n   305→      const json = await res.json();\n   306→      return (json.result?.value ?? 0) / 1_000_000_000;\n   307→    },\n   308→    { address: walletAddress, rpc: rpcUrl },\n   309→  );\n   310→}\n   311→\n   312→/**\n   313→ * Collect console errors from a page. Returns a cleanup function\n   314→ * and an array that accumulates errors.\n   315→ */\n   316→export function trackConsoleErrors(page: Page): {\n   317→  errors: string[];\n   318→  assertClean: () => void;\n   319→} {\n   320→  const errors: string[] = [];\n   321→  page.on(\"console\", (msg) => {\n   322→    if (msg.type() === \"error\") errors.push(msg.text());\n   323→  });\n   324→  return {\n   325→    errors,\n   326→    assertClean: () => {\n   327→      // Filter out known non-critical browser noise\n   328→      const real = errors.filter(\n   329→        (e) =>\n   330→          !e.includes(\"favicon.ico\") &&\n   331→          !e.includes(\"downloadable font\") &&\n   332→          !e.includes(\"third-party cookie\"),\n   333→      );\n   334→      expect(real).toEqual([]);\n   335→    },\n   336→  };\n   337→}\n   338→\n   339→/**\n   340→ * Wait for a specific text to appear anywhere on the page.\n   341→ */\n   342→export async function waitForText(\n   343→  page: Page,\n   344→  text: string,\n   345→  timeout = 10_000,\n   346→): Promise<void> {\n   347→  await expect(page.getByText(text).first()).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n   348→}\n   349→\n   350→/**\n   351→ * Wait for the lobby to be visible (no active match).\n   352→ */\n   353→export async function waitForLobby(\n   354→  page: Page,\n   355→  timeout = 15_000,\n   356→): Promise<void> {\n   357→  await page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, {\n   358→    state: \"visible\",\n   359→    timeout,\n   360→  });\n   361→}\n   362→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01E2qhRFBfUs8uq9ca1Q8VQo","session_id":"a862d5c2-6727-4db5-bc9a-88f0e3c68612","uuid":"ee69aad0-8ecf-4e56-a02b-994b39d8f3e5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E2qhRFBfUs8uq9ca1Q8VQo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the full contents of all four files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts`\n\n```ts\n/**\n * Devnet lifecycle E2E test: create → join → real VRF resolve → claim.\n *\n * Uses two isolated browser contexts (Player A and Player B) with\n * deterministic keypairs. Connects to deployed devnet programs with\n * real Orao VRF fulfillment (no mock resolve shortcut).\n *\n * Prerequisites:\n * - Coinflip + Platform programs deployed to devnet\n * - Orao VRF initialized on devnet\n * - VITE_RPC_URL, VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID set\n * - Test wallets funded on devnet (handled in beforeAll)\n */\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\nimport * as po from \"../local/helpers/page-objects\";\nimport { PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B } from \"../local/helpers/wallets\";\nimport { validateDevnetEnv } from \"./helpers/env\";\nimport { Connection, LAMPORTS_PER_SOL, type PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n```\n\nThe suite:\n- `VRF_FULFILLMENT_TIMEOUT = 90_000` ms\n- `beforeAll`: validates env, funds both test wallets via airdrop if below `MIN_BALANCE_SOL = 0.1`\n- Single test `\"coinflip devnet lifecycle: create → join → real VRF → claim\"`:\n  1. Player A navigates to `/coinflip` and creates a match (iron tier, heads)\n  2. Player A expects `.coinflip-active-match__waiting` to be visible\n  3. Player B navigates and waits for a lobby match (`waitForLobbyMatch`, 30s)\n  4. Player B joins the match\n  5. Both pages call `po.waitForResult(page, 90_000)` in parallel via `Promise.all`\n  6. Asserts exactly one winner and one loser\n  7. Winner calls `po.claimOrSettle`, then `po.backToLobby`\n  8. Loser calls `po.claimOrSettle`, then `po.backToLobby`\n  9. `consoleA.assertClean()` and `consoleB.assertClean()`\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts`\n\nFull content above (101 lines). Key points:\n\n- Extends Playwright's `base` test with `DevnetDualPlayerFixtures`\n- `devnetConfig`: calls `validateDevnetEnv()` per test\n- `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair`: sourced from `PLAYER_A` / `PLAYER_B` (deterministic)\n- `connection`: `new Connection(devnetConfig.rpcUrl, \"confirmed\")`\n- Each player gets an isolated `BrowserContext` via `createPlayerContext`, which injects `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` (first 32 bytes of keypair secret key) into the window via `addInitScript`\n- Contexts are closed after each test\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts`\n\nFull content above (179 lines). Key points:\n\n- `DevnetConfig` interface: `rpcUrl`, `network`, `coinflipProgramId`, `platformProgramId`, `oraoVrfProgramId`\n- `ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = \"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\"` (hardcoded, same on all clusters)\n- `validateDevnetEnv()`: reads `VITE_RPC_URL`, `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`, `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` from env; fails fast with consolidated error listing all missing/invalid vars; `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` is optional (default: `\"devnet\"`)\n- `verifyDevnetDeployments(config)`: async health-check — verifies RPC reachable, coinflip program executable, platform program executable, Orao VRF program executable, and Orao VRF network state PDA exists (seed: `\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\"`)\n\n---\n\n## 4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts`\n\nFull content above (362 lines). The `waitForResult` function and all polling-related helpers:\n\n### `waitForResult` (lines 223-235)\n\n```ts\n/**\n * Wait for the active match title to indicate a win or loss.\n */\nexport async function waitForResult(\n  page: Page,\n  timeout = 30_000,\n): Promise<\"won\" | \"lost\"> {\n  // Wait for either won or lost title class to appear\n  const wonLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleWon);\n  const lostLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleLost);\n\n  await expect(wonLocator.or(lostLocator)).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n\n  if (await wonLocator.isVisible()) return \"won\";\n  return \"lost\";\n}\n```\n\nUses Playwright's `.or()` combinator — no manual polling loop. Waits for either `.coinflip-active-match__title--won` or `.coinflip-active-match__title--lost` to become visible within the given timeout, then returns which one is visible.\n\n### Other wait/assert helpers\n\n- `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout=30_000)`: expects `.coinflip-sidebar__status` to have exact text\n- `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout=15_000)`: expects first non-claimable `.coinflip-match-card` to be visible\n- `waitForText(page, text, timeout=10_000)`: `page.getByText(text).first()` visible\n- `waitForLobby(page, timeout=15_000)`: `page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, state: \"visible\")`\n- `assertLobbyEmpty`: expects zero non-claimable match cards\n- `assertErrorToast` / `assertNoErrorToast`: toast visibility checks\n- `getSolBalance`: RPC `getBalance` call via `page.evaluate` (not UI polling)\n- `trackConsoleErrors`: attaches `page.on(\"console\")` listener, `assertClean()` filters known noise (favicon, font, third-party cookie errors)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a201c56400f60bc71 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 39304\ntool_uses: 4\nduration_ms: 39344</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a862d5c2-6727-4db5-bc9a-88f0e3c68612","uuid":"7e314fd9-2a13-4ba2-9ea6-783b8a5475d5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read and return the full contents of these files:\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts`\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts`\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts`\n4. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts` (specifically the waitForResult function and any polling-related helpers)\n\nReturn the full file contents for each.","agentId":"a201c56400f60bc71","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the full contents of all four files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts`\n\n```ts\n/**\n * Devnet lifecycle E2E test: create → join → real VRF resolve → claim.\n *\n * Uses two isolated browser contexts (Player A and Player B) with\n * deterministic keypairs. Connects to deployed devnet programs with\n * real Orao VRF fulfillment (no mock resolve shortcut).\n *\n * Prerequisites:\n * - Coinflip + Platform programs deployed to devnet\n * - Orao VRF initialized on devnet\n * - VITE_RPC_URL, VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID set\n * - Test wallets funded on devnet (handled in beforeAll)\n */\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\nimport * as po from \"../local/helpers/page-objects\";\nimport { PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B } from \"../local/helpers/wallets\";\nimport { validateDevnetEnv } from \"./helpers/env\";\nimport { Connection, LAMPORTS_PER_SOL, type PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n```\n\nThe suite:\n- `VRF_FULFILLMENT_TIMEOUT = 90_000` ms\n- `beforeAll`: validates env, funds both test wallets via airdrop if below `MIN_BALANCE_SOL = 0.1`\n- Single test `\"coinflip devnet lifecycle: create → join → real VRF → claim\"`:\n  1. Player A navigates to `/coinflip` and creates a match (iron tier, heads)\n  2. Player A expects `.coinflip-active-match__waiting` to be visible\n  3. Player B navigates and waits for a lobby match (`waitForLobbyMatch`, 30s)\n  4. Player B joins the match\n  5. Both pages call `po.waitForResult(page, 90_000)` in parallel via `Promise.all`\n  6. Asserts exactly one winner and one loser\n  7. Winner calls `po.claimOrSettle`, then `po.backToLobby`\n  8. Loser calls `po.claimOrSettle`, then `po.backToLobby`\n  9. `consoleA.assertClean()` and `consoleB.assertClean()`\n\n---\n\n## 2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts`\n\nFull content above (101 lines). Key points:\n\n- Extends Playwright's `base` test with `DevnetDualPlayerFixtures`\n- `devnetConfig`: calls `validateDevnetEnv()` per test\n- `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair`: sourced from `PLAYER_A` / `PLAYER_B` (deterministic)\n- `connection`: `new Connection(devnetConfig.rpcUrl, \"confirmed\")`\n- Each player gets an isolated `BrowserContext` via `createPlayerContext`, which injects `__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` (first 32 bytes of keypair secret key) into the window via `addInitScript`\n- Contexts are closed after each test\n\n---\n\n## 3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts`\n\nFull content above (179 lines). Key points:\n\n- `DevnetConfig` interface: `rpcUrl`, `network`, `coinflipProgramId`, `platformProgramId`, `oraoVrfProgramId`\n- `ORAO_VRF_PROGRAM_ID = \"VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y\"` (hardcoded, same on all clusters)\n- `validateDevnetEnv()`: reads `VITE_RPC_URL`, `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID`, `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` from env; fails fast with consolidated error listing all missing/invalid vars; `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` is optional (default: `\"devnet\"`)\n- `verifyDevnetDeployments(config)`: async health-check — verifies RPC reachable, coinflip program executable, platform program executable, Orao VRF program executable, and Orao VRF network state PDA exists (seed: `\"orao-vrf-network-configuration\"`)\n\n---\n\n## 4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/page-objects.ts`\n\nFull content above (362 lines). The `waitForResult` function and all polling-related helpers:\n\n### `waitForResult` (lines 223-235)\n\n```ts\n/**\n * Wait for the active match title to indicate a win or loss.\n */\nexport async function waitForResult(\n  page: Page,\n  timeout = 30_000,\n): Promise<\"won\" | \"lost\"> {\n  // Wait for either won or lost title class to appear\n  const wonLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleWon);\n  const lostLocator = page.locator(sel.activeMatchTitleLost);\n\n  await expect(wonLocator.or(lostLocator)).toBeVisible({ timeout });\n\n  if (await wonLocator.isVisible()) return \"won\";\n  return \"lost\";\n}\n```\n\nUses Playwright's `.or()` combinator — no manual polling loop. Waits for either `.coinflip-active-match__title--won` or `.coinflip-active-match__title--lost` to become visible within the given timeout, then returns which one is visible.\n\n### Other wait/assert helpers\n\n- `waitForPhaseLabel(page, label, timeout=30_000)`: expects `.coinflip-sidebar__status` to have exact text\n- `waitForLobbyMatch(page, timeout=15_000)`: expects first non-claimable `.coinflip-match-card` to be visible\n- `waitForText(page, text, timeout=10_000)`: `page.getByText(text).first()` visible\n- `waitForLobby(page, timeout=15_000)`: `page.waitForSelector(sel.lobby, state: \"visible\")`\n- `assertLobbyEmpty`: expects zero non-claimable match cards\n- `assertErrorToast` / `assertNoErrorToast`: toast visibility checks\n- `getSolBalance`: RPC `getBalance` call via `page.evaluate` (not UI polling)\n- `trackConsoleErrors`: attaches `page.on(\"console\")` listener, `assertClean()` filters known noise (favicon, font, third-party cookie errors)"}],"totalDurationMs":39344,"totalTokens":39304,"totalToolUseCount":4,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13051,"cache_read_input_tokens":24544,"output_tokens":1708,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13051,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
